The heart of the first
map looks like this.

00:08:40.799 --> 00:08:43.090
As you might imagine,
the "plus" signs

00:08:43.090 --> 00:08:45.860
identify opportunities
for expansion.

00:08:45.860 --> 00:08:48.590
If you click on a "plus"
sign, it will open additional

00:08:48.590 --> 00:08:52.910
branches of the map -- like so.

00:08:52.910 --> 00:08:55.570
These icons identify links.

00:08:55.570 --> 00:08:58.160
Some of the links will
open slide presentations

00:08:58.160 --> 00:08:59.280
that I have prepared.

00:08:59.280 --> 00:09:03.250
Others lead to copies of
statutes or judicial decisions

00:09:03.250 --> 00:09:06.570
-- or to supplementary materials
prepared by other scholars

00:09:06.570 --> 00:09:10.580
or lawyers that are accessible
through the Internet.

00:09:10.580 --> 00:09:14.060
The second map, which examines
Intellectual Property Theory,

00:09:14.060 --> 00:09:17.200
works the same way.

00:09:17.200 --> 00:09:20.400
Both of the maps were created
using the Mindmanager software

00:09:20.400 --> 00:09:23.530
program, and I will be
displaying the Mindmanager

00:09:23.530 --> 00:09:26.380
versions on your screens
during these lectures.

00:09:26.380 --> 00:09:29.020
If you want to explore
the maps at your leisure,

00:09:29.020 --> 00:09:32.650
you can gain access to them
through the CopyrightX website

00:09:32.650 --> 00:09:35.830
or through my personal
homepage, the address of which

00:09:35.830 --> 00:09:38.010
is: tfisher.org.

00:09:38.010 --> 00:09:41.720
If you want to edit the
maps, for example, to add

00:09:41.720 --> 00:09:44.200
